sequenceDiagram
    actor A as Administrator
    participant FE as React<br/>AdminUsersPage
    participant API1 as DRF<br/>AdminSuspendUserView
    participant API2 as DRF<br/>AdminUnsuspendUserView
    participant Audit as _log_admin_action()
    participant Perm as IsAdmin
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    A->>FE: Click "Suspend" on user row
    FE->>API1: POST /api/accounts/admin/users/{id}/suspend/ {reason}
    API1->>Perm: has_permission(request)
    Perm-->>API1: Allowed
    API1->>DB: CustomUser.objects.get(pk=id)
    DB-->>API1: User instance
    API1->>DB: user.suspend(reason=reason)
    DB-->>API1: User suspended
    API1->>Audit: _log_admin_action(admin, "suspend_user", target_user)
    Audit->>DB: AuditLog.objects.create(action, admin, target, reason)
    API1-->>FE: 200 OK {user_id, is_suspended: true}
    FE-->>U: User status updated to "Suspended"
    Note over A,FE: Later, admin unsuspends
    A->>FE: Click "Unsuspend" on user row
    FE->>API2: POST /api/accounts/admin/users/{id}/unsuspend/
    API2->>DB: user.unsuspend()
    API2->>Audit: _log_admin_action(admin, "unsuspend_user", target_user)
    Audit->>DB: AuditLog.objects.create(...)
    API2-->>FE: 200 OK {user_id, is_suspended: false}
    FE-->>U: User status updated to "Active"
